com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.bootstrapui.elements

Class ViewElementFieldset

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.web.ui.elements.ContainerViewElement
      • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.views.bootstrapui.elements.ViewElementFieldset
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.foreach.across.modules.web.ui.MutableViewElement, com.foreach.across.modules.web.ui.ViewElement

    public class ViewElementFieldset
extends com.foreach.across.modules.web.ui.elements.ContainerViewElement
    Represents a fieldset of other ViewElement objects. A fieldset has for ContainerViewElement properties:
    • getTitle(): contains elements that make up the title of the fieldset
    • getHeader(): contains elements that appear before the body, usually additional information about the fieldset as a whole
    • getBody(): contains the actual fields that make up the fieldset
    • getFooter(): contains elements that appear after the body, usually additional information about the fieldset as a whole

    How a ViewElementFieldset is rendered depends on the setTemplate(Function) that has been set. By default all content will be rendered in an actual HTML fieldset element. A number of default templates are also available: TEMPLATE_BODY_ONLY, TEMPLATE_SECTION_H1, TEMPLATE_SECTION_H2, TEMPLATE_SECTION_H3, TEMPLATE_PANEL_DEFAULT, TEMPLATE_PANEL_INFO, TEMPLATE_PANEL_PRIMARY, TEMPLATE_PANEL_SUCCESS, TEMPLATE_PANEL_WARNING and TEMPLATE_PANEL_DANGER.

    See also the utility functions for manually generating simple templates:

    • structureTemplate(String, String)
    • panelTemplate(String, Style)

    Any child element operations (adding, removing) performed directly on the ViewElementFieldset, will actually be performed on the body container instead.

    NOTE: This class does not represent a FieldsetFormElement which always renders a HTML fieldset. An HTML fieldset will also be rendered if no specific template is set, but the ViewElementFieldset is a general abstraction.

    Since:
    3.2.0
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
    See Also:
    FieldsetElementBuilderFactory

      • TEMPLATE_FIELDSET

        public static final Function<ViewElementFieldset,? extends com.foreach.across.modules.web.ui.ViewElement> TEMPLATE_FIELDSET
        Template that renders the fieldset as an actual HTML fieldset element with only a legend. An additional class element-fieldset-fieldset will be put on the outer wrapper. The body of the fieldset will not be wrapped to stay compatible with the equivalent FieldsetFormElement output. See the structureTemplate(String, String) documentation for information on the other CSS classes added.

        NOTE: this is the default rendering template.

      • structureTemplate

        public static Function<ViewElementFieldset,com.foreach.across.modules.web.ui.elements.NodeViewElement> structureTemplate(@NonNull
                                                                                                                         @NonNull String cssClassName,
                                                                                                                         @NonNull
                                                                                                                         @NonNull String structure)
        Generate a template function that outputs a simple HTML structure based on a structure string. The structure can be any of the following:
        • wrapper: a single outer element wrapper will be added
        • wrapper/title: in addition to the wrapper, the title will be wrapped with a title element
        • wrapper/title/content: additionally the content (header+body+footer) will be wrapped with a content element
        • wrapper/title/header/body/footer: the content will not be wrapped as a whole, but every component will be wrapped separately
        • wrapper/title/content/header/body/footer: all components will be wrapped separately, and header/body/footer will additionally be wrapped with a content element
        This template will also add the following CSS classes to the output:
        • element-fieldset: to the outer fieldset wrapper element
        • element-fieldset-title: to the title wrapper element
        • element-fieldset-content: to the content wrapper element
        • element-fieldset-header: to the header wrapper element
        • element-fieldset-body: to the body wrapper
        • element-fieldset-footer: to the footer wrapper element
        For example a format of section/h1/div with a cssClassName='my-custom-css' will output the following: 
        
 <section class="element-fieldset my-custom-css">
     <h1 class="element-fieldset-title">[title elements]</h1>
     <div class="element-fieldset-content">
         [header elements]
         [body elements]
         [footer elements]
     </div>
 </section>
        Parameters:
        cssClassName - additional css class that should be added to the outer wrapper
        structure - string
        Returns:
        template function

      • panelTemplate

        public static Function<ViewElementFieldset,com.foreach.across.modules.web.ui.elements.NodeViewElement> panelTemplate(@NonNull
                                                                                                                     @NonNull String cssClassName,
                                                                                                                     @NonNull
                                                                                                                     @NonNull Style style)
        Generate a template function that builds a Bootstrap panel layout for the fieldset. Heading and footer panel elements will only be added if their content is not empty.

        This template will also add the following CSS classes to the output:

        • element-fieldset: to the main panel div
        • element-fieldset-title: to the panel heading
        • element-fieldset-body: to the panel body
        • element-fieldset-header: to an additional div wrapping the header element (inside panel body)
        • element-fieldset-body: to an additional div wrapping the body element (inside panel body)
        • element-fieldset-footer: to the panel footer
        For example a format of Style.DANGER with a cssClassName='my-custom-css' will output the following: 
        
 <div class="element-fieldset my-custom-css panel panel-danger">
  <div class="element-fieldset-title panel-heading">[title elements]</div>
  <div class="element-fieldset-content panel-body">
      <div class="element-fieldset-header">[header elements]</div>
      <div class="element-fieldset-body">[body elements]</div>
  </div>
  <div class="element-fieldset-footer panel-footer">[footer elements]</div>
 </div>
        Parameters:
        cssClassName - additional css class that should be added to the main panel div
        style - panel style
        Returns:
        template function
